verbose_text: XREF_BIBR We assessed steady-state levels of the human homologs OXA1L and TIMM22 in skeletal muscle samples from affected individuals but in contrast to the reports in yeast, OXA1L and TIMM22 were markedly increased in affected subjects relative to control subjects (XREF_FIG), suggesting that the lower levels of AAC1 in the affected individuals cannot be explained by loss of the protein import machinery.
